<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-25T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-25T16:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4713: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Magruder</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-25T22:00:00+01:00">July 25, 1931—10
                                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 25—9:05
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                                <p>28. My telegram No. 27, July 24, 8 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d190fn27">Not printed.</note> Following
                                    communication published this morning: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“On the 18th instant official notification was given of
                                            acceptance in principle by the Portuguese Government of
                                            the Hoover proposal with certain reservations relating
                                            primarily to the reparations in kind which have special
                                            importance for Portugal. There has been sent to London a
                                            Portuguese expert who is handling the matter there.”</p>
                                    </quote></p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Magruder</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>